{"TopicId":165382,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Plugin to make the camera in the VAB behave the same as in the SPH?","CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T04:10:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T04:10:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like a plugin that swaps the scroll wheel, and scroll wheel\u002Bshift functions in the\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E so that it operates the same way\u00A0in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0Having built around 90% of my craft in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0it feels like entering an alien world going into the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- To clarify, the WASD editor camera is not what I\u0027m looking for; I simply want the scroll wheel, and scroll wheel\u002Bshift functions to be swapped.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-11T07:41:36Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2017 07:41  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Avera9eJoe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T04:37:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, but use an alternative launch site mod(to override the Runway launch site).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T05:05:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505104641\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Blaarkies\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, Blaarkies said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E, but use an alternative launch site mod(to override the Runway launch site).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would except I run into the problem that rockets don\u0027t fit vertically in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T07:24:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\neven better IMO:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6350190828\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/121386-13-wasd-editor-camera-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T07:38:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170051\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505114681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Drew Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Drew Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\neven better IMO:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1552542053\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/121386-13-wasd-editor-camera-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:213px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s plugin is\u00A0incredible \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0Still though it\u0027s more of an addon to building that reworking the stock ones. It\u00A0doesn\u0027t effect quick vertical movement the way holding shift does. I\u0027d like a plugin that makes holding shift move vertically the same way that it does in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0so both builders\u00A0operate the same.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-11T07:43:14Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2017 07:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Avera9eJoe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T08:26:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505106322\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280363\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Avera9eJoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Avera9eJoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would except I run into the problem that rockets don\u0027t fit vertically in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yes of course. I just always build mine sideways, keep an eye on the radial/symmetry settings, and when i am done just shift-click the craft, flip it upright and launch(on load the game will figure out how to not put it underground)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nPrefer it since it is a lot easier to get into tight spaces, like adding payload inside fairings or cargo bays, building a quick rover that will serve a 10 seconds purpose after landing. It is also a lot more spacious(great for planning the majority of a moon base before sending up the pieces), and then building pieces to land on the Mun horizontally is much easier in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI see you make some cool youtube videos, so i have to admit maybe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E isn\u0027t the solution. Your viewers probably want\u00A0something familiar like the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E they are used to. I didnt like the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E at first, only after \u0022finishing\u0022 my first career did i start experimenting in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E...and after the pay-to-upgrade \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003Eksc\u003C/abbr\u003E buildings update, i quickly realized that i could save money by only upgrading the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E/runway. This way i can launch rockets and planes for the price of one building\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-09-11T17:53:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223170056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022165382\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221505115534\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280363\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Avera9eJoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Avera9eJoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u00A0doesn\u0027t effect quick vertical movement the way holding shift does.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit\u0027s got modifier keys that lets you move fast or crawl slow and can be adjusted. So when I hold Shift and press Q my view zips right up. Easier on my mouse hand too than working the scroll wheel constantly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-09-11T17:53:26Z\u0022 title=\u002209/11/2017 05:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Drew Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}